REASONING: Authoritative Land Transport Authority (LTA) page shows the East-West Line is the Green line ("East-West Line (Green)"). This establishes what the "green line" refers to in Singapore's MRT.

SBS Transit station information for Chinatown clearly lists the station under the North East Line (purple) and the Downtown Line (blue). The page header shows "Train Line Downtown Line Blue / North East Line Purple" and the station entry is for Chinatown, confirming Chinatown is on those lines, not the East-West (green) line.
A travel guide summary of Singapore MRT line colours lists East West Line as Green, North East Line as Purple and Downtown Line as Blue—supporting the mapping of colours to line names used above.

Therefore the statement "Chinatown MRT is on the green line" is incorrect for Singapore: Chinatown MRT station is on the North East Line (purple) and Downtown Line (blue), not the green East-West Line.
